      <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
      <p>By accessing and using the National Secure Storage &mdash; Jeffrey's Bay website and services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.</p>

      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>National Secure Storage provides self-storage rental services for individuals and businesses. Our services include online unit reservations, secure payment processing, and access to storage facilities at 35 St Croix Street, Jeffrey's Bay, Eastern Cape, 6330.</p>

      <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>You must be at least 18 years old to use our services. By registering, you represent that you are of legal age and have the authority to enter into a binding agreement.</p>

      <h2>4. Storage Unit Rental</h2>
      <p>Rental agreements are month-to-month unless a longer term is selected at booking. Available terms are 1, 3, 6, and 12 months. Pricing is displayed on our website and is subject to change with 30 days' notice.</p>
      <p>Units are rented on a first-come, first-served basis. Availability is indicated on our website but is subject to change.</p>

      <h2>5. Payment Terms</h2>
      <p>Payments are processed securely online. All prices are in South African Rand (ZAR). Payment must be made in advance for the selected rental term. Late payments may result in loss of access to your unit.</p>
      <p>We accept Visa and Mastercard credit cards. Debit cards are not accepted for online payments at this time.</p>

      <h2>6. Access and Hours</h2>
      <p>Access to the storage facility is available during the following hours:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Monday to Friday: 08:00 &ndash; 17:00</li>
        <li>Saturday: 09:00 &ndash; 13:00</li>
        <li>Sunday and Public Holidays: Closed</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Hours may change seasonally. We will provide notice of any changes.</p>

      <h2>7. Prohibited Items</h2>
      <p>You may not store the following items in your unit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Perishable goods, food, or living plants</li>
        <li>Flammable or explosive materials</li>
        <li>Hazardous chemicals or substances</li>
        <li>Illegal goods or materials</li>
        <li>Radioactive materials</li>
        <li>Asbestos or toxic waste</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Security and Liability</h2>
      <p>While our facility is equipped with 24/7 CCTV surveillance and perimeter security, National Secure Storage is not responsible for loss or damage to stored items due to theft, fire, flood, or other events beyond our control. We strongly recommend that you obtain insurance for valuable items.</p>
      <p>You are responsible for providing your own padlock for your unit.</p>

      <h2>9. Cancellation and Termination</h2>
      <p>You may cancel your rental at any time by providing 30 days' written notice (email acceptable). Refunds are calculated on a pro-rata basis for unused days of the rental period. A R150 cancellation admin fee applies to monthly contracts.</p>

      <h2>10. Right of Entry</h2>
      <p>We reserve the right to enter your storage unit in the following circumstances:</p>
